---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Tree Removal Gosford | Arborist, Lopping & Stump Grinding"
  description="Tree services in Gosford — removal, lopping & pruning, stump grinding and storm work by qualified arborists. Mature street-tree canopy, hillside removals, Central Coast Council permit help. Free quote."
  canonical="https://centralcoasttreeservice.com.au/gosford/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Gosford &middot; East Gosford &middot; Point Clare &middot; West Gosford</span>
      <h1>Tree services in <span class="accent">Gosford</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Gosford is the Central Coast's council seat and one of its leafiest urban
        areas &mdash; mature street-tree canopy, established gardens and a lot of
        steep, hillside blocks running up off the waterfront. Tree removal,
        lopping, stump grinding and storm work by qualified arborists who know the
        Central Coast Council permit rules. Free written quote on site.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Tree work in Gosford</span>
      <h2>What we do around Gosford.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Mature canopy &mdash; and the permit that protects it.</h3>
        <p>
          As the Central Coast's administrative centre, Gosford and its older
          surrounds (East Gosford, Point Clare, Springfield) carry a heavy
          <strong>mature street-tree and backyard canopy</strong> &mdash; spotted gum,
          angophora, brush box, jacaranda and big old camphor laurels. Most of these
          established trees on private land are <strong>protected</strong> under
          Central Coast Council's Tree and Vegetation Management controls, so removal
          or heavy pruning generally needs an approved Private Tree Works application
          first. We tell you up front whether your tree is exempt (dead, declared
          weed, genuine imminent risk) or needs a permit, and we can write the
          arborist report Council needs. If you're unsure, Council's number is
          (02) 4306 7900.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Hillside removals &mdash; the Gosford specialty.</h3>
        <p>
          A lot of Gosford's housing climbs the hills behind the CBD and around
          Brisbane Water, which means <strong>steep, tight, terraced blocks</strong>
          with difficult machine access and trees that have to come down over a house
          or down a slope. That's sectional dismantling and careful rigging work, not
          a straight fell &mdash; we plan drop zones, use climbing arborists and bring a
          crane where access allows. See <a href="/services/tree-removal/">tree
          removal</a> for how we take big trees down safely on confined sites.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Pruning, deadwooding and storm clean-up.</h3>
        <p>
          Plenty of Gosford trees don't need removing &mdash; they need a proper
          <a href="/services/tree-lopping/">prune to AS 4373</a>: crown thinning to
          let wind through, deadwooding the limbs most likely to fail, and clearance
          off roofs and powerlines. After an East Coast Low we're busy with
          <a href="/services/emergency-tree-removal/">storm clean-up</a> across the
          Gosford basin, where saturated hillsides and big old gums make for fallen
          limbs and lifted root plates.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Gosford jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Sectional removal of a large spotted gum on a steep East Gosford block, crane-assisted</li>
          <li>Crown thinning and deadwooding a row of angophoras over a Point Clare roofline</li>
          <li>Private Tree Works arborist report for a protected camphor laurel removal</li>
          <li>Stump grinding after removal so the hillside terrace can be re-turfed</li>
          <li>Emergency make-safe on a storm-felled limb across a West Gosford driveway</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/terrigal/">Terrigal</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/wyong/">Wyong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/erina/">Erina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woy-woy/">Woy Woy</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/central-coast-region/">All Central Coast Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Gosford tree quote.</h2>
        <p>Hillside-removal specialists. Permit advice included. 24/7 for storm emergencies.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
